The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Bengal | Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   BRIEFS
                  
	Siliguri, April 14: A 20-year-old yesterday stabbed his teenaged girlfriend repeatedly after she tried to end their affair and rejected his Poila Boishak gift. The 16-year-old from Jalpaiguri, who appeared for Madhyamik this year, is in a critical condition.    
	Niranjan Rongdar alias Tinku, her boyfriend, has been arrested.    
	Last night, the girl was returning home with a friend when she met Tinku. He offered her a gift and a card, which she rejected and told him to end the affair, a police officer said. When she stuck to her stand despite his repeated pleas, the youth took out a knife and stabbed her.        
	Midnapore: A 35-year-old man in West Midnapore killed his mother and brother on Monday after his sibling accused him of having an affair with his wife. Subal, the younger brother of Nabin Soren, lost his cool when his brother brought the charge against him. When mother Alladi intervened, Subal hit both with a sharp object, killing them on the spot.        
	Durgapur: Some 25 people were injured, seven seriously, in a clash between villagers. Residents of Kejekura in Bankura attacked villagers from Molbona over a case of alleged eve teasing.                                                                                                                                                                   
